110.name: God Save The Key
110.description:
‚ÄúGod Save The Key‚Äù by artist YuYu takes a spin on renaissance masterpieces to humourlessly remind us the importance of self sovereignty - Not your Keys, Not your coins. YuYu's reinterpretation of Jacques-Louis David's painting The Oath of the Horatii (1786) draws inspiration from the three depicted brothers and their unity, reflecting the collective efforts of the web3 community to defend and uphold its ethos.   
   
Additionally, the artwork combines elements from Karl Brullov's The Last Day of Pompeii (1833), lighting with its eruption the left corner of the background, and Briton Riviere's lions from Daniel's Answer to the King (1892) encircle the main character, serving as indicators of imminent danger. Through these conceptual elements, the work depicts the turbulent nature of cryptocurrency while emphasizing the vital role of unity and collective action in fortifying decentralization.  
   
Artworks used:   
1. The Oath of the Horatii 1786 - Jacques-Louis David   
2. The Last Day of Pompeii 1833 - Karl Brullov   
3. Daniel's Answer To The King 1892 - Briton Riviere   
  
Meme: 10  
Season: 3

115.name: Vital Energy
115.description:
"Vital Energy" is a piece of art that captivates the imagination with its visual narrative and its emotive message. The protagonist of this story is a child named Jonny Boy, a curious and adventurous soul who transcends the limitations of reality.   
   
The artwork opens with Jonny Boy gracefully soaring amidst the clouds, arms spread wide like wings, his gaze filled with wonder and fear at the same time. This image symbolizes childhood, a time of discovery and uncertainty where every moment is a new adventure.   
   
However, the scene takes an unexpected turn when Jonny Boy is struck by a cascade of arrows materializing out of nowhere.  This detail emphasizes that even when Jonny Boy faces challenges and obstacles, he must maintain faith in himself and his journey. JonnyBoy represents each of us struggling and enduring to improve this difficult world.    
   
I dedicated this work to WAGMI because this phrase is magical, it unites people in a feeling of belonging and mutual support. When you say or share this acronym, you create a bond with others who share the same spirit of determination and confidence in the future.   
  
Meme: 2  
Season: 3  
Card: 3

119.name: Equilibrium
119.description:
In the heart of the abyss stands a monolith-like structure, representing a scale, a balance between both worlds with its "weights" extending on both sides.   
   
The left side, a vibrant depiction of nature unfolds, captivating the essence of real-life experiences and fundamental rights, evoking a connection to our physical world.   
   
The right side of the scale however, takes on a digital persona. This realm represents the realm of Digital Rights, where the virtual realm intertwines with our daily lives.   
   
We witness the delicate balance between real-world and digital rights, where one cannot exist without the other, emphasizing the imperative to value each sphere equally. A profound reminder that compromising either realm would undermine the harmonious coexistence of these vital aspects of our lives.   
   
TLDR; SEIZE THE RIGHTS OF DIGITALIZATION   
   
Meme: 11   
Season: 4
